WRITING.TITLE: My biggest secret
WRITING.TEXT: I #8217;m going to tell you my story and I #8217;m really scared to do so but I need to. Two years ago I developed some mental issues (and I #8217;ve also had smaller shit like insomnia for a very long time) but two years ago it wasn #8217;t that bad. I was just sad. I had a friend that I would talk to every Tuesday about my family life and other shit. But we stopped doing that, and so I just bottled shit up. Six months ago I got my first job as a host in a restaurant and I fell into a hole of depression. It was really bad, I couldn #8217;t get out of my bed, I was constantly thinking about it to the point it would make me physically ill. It wasn #8217;t about the job, i don #8217;t even know what happened, something just...changed in me. Even thinking about it now makes me want to cry. Anyways, after the first three months, I started getting better, I made some kind of new friends and was feeling ok. But then quarantine came. The restaurant is closed, so that is off my mind. But my home life isn #8217;t the best and two weeks ago me and my mom got in a fight and I had so much emotional pain that I cut myself four times so that I could focus on the physical pain instead of the emotional. And it felt freeing, because I wasn #8217;t focused on my insides, and I hate myself a lot. But now I do it every night and I need it because sometimes the pain is too much. I just need life to go back to normal and I need the pain to go away. And I can #8217;t tell anyone but you guys because my mom has anxiety and she wouldn #8217;t be able to handle that burden at the moment.
